.SH LS COMMAND MAPPING
How lsbin commands map to ls options:
.SS l. (Dotfiles Only)
.RS
.EX
lsbin l.

# Equivalent to:
ls --color=auto -hA | grep --color=auto '^\.'
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
-h: Human-readable file sizes (K, M, G)
.IP \(bu 2
-A: Show all files except . and ..
.IP \(bu 2
Filtered to show only entries starting with dot
.IP \(bu 2
Useful for inspecting configuration files
.RE
.SS ls (Standard Listing)
.RS
.EX
lsbin ls

# Equivalent to:
ls --color=auto -hA
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
-h: Human-readable file sizes
.IP \(bu 2
-A: Show almost all (except . and ..)
.IP \(bu 2
--color=auto: Colored output
.IP \(bu 2
Shows all files including hidden
.RE
.SS la (List All)
.RS
.EX
lsbin la

# Equivalent to:
ls --color=auto -hA
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Same as ls command
.IP \(bu 2
Mnemonic: la = list all
.IP \(bu 2
Includes hidden files
.IP \(bu 2
Human-readable sizes
.RE
.SS ll (Long Listing)
.RS
.EX
lsbin ll

# Equivalent to:
ls --color=auto -hl
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
-h: Human-readable file sizes
.IP \(bu 2
-l: Long format (permissions, owner, size, date)
.IP \(bu 2
Does NOT show hidden files (no -A)
.IP \(bu 2
Useful for permission inspection
.RE
.SS lla (Long List All)
.RS
.EX
lsbin lla

# Equivalent to:
ls --color=auto -hlA
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
-h: Human-readable file sizes
.IP \(bu 2
-l: Long format
.IP \(bu 2
-A: Show almost all files
.IP \(bu 2
Complete directory view with details
.RE
.SS dir (Directories Only)
.RS
.EX
lsbin dir

# Equivalent to:
ls --color=auto -hD
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
-h: Human-readable sizes
.IP \(bu 2
-D: List directories only (not contents)
.IP \(bu 2
Useful for quick directory overview
.IP \(bu 2
Shows only subdirectories in current path
.RE
